Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of throughput distributions in CSMA wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of analytical techniques and observations, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of a theory to explain the back-of-the-envelope computation method, which could fall under cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the paper mentions that the techniques and results developed could be applicable to other physical and engineering systems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
